    "https://gs1-epcis-reg.org/rail/rail-context.jsonld",
    "https://ref.openepcis.io/extensions/common/interop/rail-bridge-context.jsonld"
  ],
  "type": "EPCISDocument",
  "schemaVersion": "2.0",
  "creationDate": "2026-05-07T08:14:00.000Z",
  "_comment_architecture": [
    "Wayside Train Monitoring System (WTMS) heat-detection event for a freight wagon.",
    "Rail-specific sensor metadata (rail:typeWtms = HFO, rail:visibility = Public,",
    "rail:sideIndicator) and sensor report fields (rail:wheelTemperature,",
    "rail:bearingTemperature, rail:normalizedAxle, rail:leftValue, rail:rightValue)",
    "ride at event level inside sensorElementList — the EPCIS-native place for sensor",
    "observations.",
    "",
    "rail:visibility carries the bare value 'Public', which the rail-bridge-context",
    "expands to oec:Public via the @vocab term coercion. A consumer that has the",
    "bridge in scope sees a oec:AccessLevel hit; one that doesn't sees the rail enum.",
    "",
    "masterDataAvailableFor carries gs1:-only product master data (productName, gtin,",
    "netWeight) per the EPCIS extension rule. rail: properties never go inside it.",
    "",
    "HTTP header (REQUIRED for an OpenEPCIS repository to engage rail-specific",
    "validation against Rail-EPCIS-SHACL-Generic.json):",
    "  GS1-Extensions: rail=https://gs1-epcis-reg.org/rail/voc/data#, oec=https://ref.openepcis.io/extensions/common/core/",
    "",
    "GS1 demo prefix 952. Wagon EPC encodes a rail vehicle identifier via GIAI-style",
    "Digital Link (8004 AI)."
  ],
